712497f-a.text:
W. 38th Street, west from Broadway to Seventh Avenue, as viewed across the low structures at the N.W. corner of Broadway and 38th Street to show prominently the 43 storied Navarre Mercantile Building, (No. 512-Seventh Avenue). At the left is the 23 story Bricken Broadway Building (No. 1385 Broadway) and to the right the Fashion Center Building (525 Seventh Avenue). The majority of the property shown, both low and tall structures, are holdings of the Wendell family.
May 7, 1930
P.L. Sperr
